liquid.logger

Class LiquidFileWriter

  • java.lang.Object
    • liquid.logger.LiquidFileWriter

  • public class LiquidFileWriter
extends java.lang.Object
    Class is used to write the log files of a simulation. This includes the parameters as well as the individual particles, flow meters, and breakpoints data, provided by the Engine.

      • writeLogParam

        public void writeLogParam(java.lang.String[] args)
        Method writes the contents of the String[] onto a text file. This represents the log file, which stores all parameter information for future replaying.
        Parameters:
        args - - the String[] of parameters

      • writeLogData

        public void writeLogData(java.lang.String[] args)
        Method used to add a string of data into the log file, all in one line.

        PRECONDITION: initLogFile() method MUST be called successfully at some point prior to calling this function.

        Parameters:
        args - - String[] to be written into the log file
